article.headline: Colgate 71, Holy Cross 65
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Alvin Reed had 19 points and seven assists to lead Colgate over Holy Cross 71-65 Wednesday night. After trailing 35-31 at halftime, Holy Cross took a 46-42 lead with 13:29 left before Colgate tied it at 48-48 on Mark Linebaugh's 3-pointer. The Raiders scored the next 11 points to take the lead for good. Linebaugh had 13 points for Colgate (8-6). Nate Lufkin led Holy Cross (7-8) with 15 points, and John Hurley added 14 points and seven rebounds.
